-----
EASTER TRIDUUM
OF THE PASSION AND RESURRECTION
OF THE LORD

THURSDAY OF THE LORD'S SUPPER

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
READING:    Heb 13:12-15    

MAGNIFICAT:	While they were at supper, Jesus took bread, said the blessing, broke the bread and gave it to his disciples.

PRAYER:	O God, who have called us to participate in this most sacred Supper, in which your Only Begotten Son, when about to hand himself over to death, entrusted to the Church a sacrifice new for all eternity, the banquet of his love, grant, we pray, that we may draw from so great a mystery, the fullness of charity and of life. Through our Lord Jesus Christ, your Son, who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever.

Compline from Sunday, after Second Vespers

GOOD FRIDAY

INVITATORY
Come, let us worship Christ, the Son of God, who redeemed us with his blood.

VIGILS
PSALMODY
Ps 2 - Ps 21 - Ps 37

LAUDS
READING:    Is 52:13-15    

BENEDICTUS:	Over his head they hung their accusation: Jesus of Nazareth, King of the Jews.

PRAYER:	O God, who by the Passion of Christ your Son, our Lord, abolished the death inherited from ancient sin by every succeeding generation, grant that just as, being conformed to him, we have borne by the law of nature the image of the man of earth, so by the sanctification of grace we may bear the image of the Man of heaven. Through Christ our Lord.

SEXT
PSALMODY
Ps 35 - Ps 53 - Ps 87

READING:    Is 53:4-5    
Lord, remember me.
- When you come into your kingdom.

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
PSALMODY
Ps 115 - Ps 141 - Ps 142 - NT 5

READING:    1 Pet 2:21-24    

MAGNIFICAT:	When we were his enemies , God reconciled us to himself by the death of his Son.

Compline from Sunday, after Second Vespers

HOLY SATURDAY

INVITATORY
Come, let us worship Christ, who for our sake suffered death and was buried.

VIGILS
PSALMODY
Ps 4 - Ps 15 - Ps 23

LAUDS
PSALMODY
Ps 63 ant. Lent - Ps 76 ant. OT - OT 23 ant. Lent - Ps 150 (Per.) ant. OT

READING:    Hosea 5:15b-16:2    

BENEDICTUS:	Save us, O Savior of the world. On the cross you redeemed us by the shedding of your blood; we cry out for your help, O God.

PRAYER:	Remember your mercies, O Lord, and with your eternal protection sanctify your servants, for whom Christ your Son, by the shedding of his Blood, established the Paschal Mystery. Who lives and reigns for ever and ever.

SEXT
PSALMODY
Ps 26 ant. Chr. - Ps 29 ant. Lent - Ps 75 ant. Lent

READING:    1 Jn 2:1b-2    

The Lord kills and gives life.
- He thrusts men down to hell and raises them up again.

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
PSALMODY & ANTIPHONS of Good Friday

READING:    1 Pet 1:18-21    

MAGNIFICAT:	Now the Son of Man has been glorified and God has been glorifid in him.

Compline from Sunday, after Second Vespers. It is said only by those who do not participate in the Easter Vigil.
